                <article id="spoontheory">
                    <h3>Spoon Theory</h3>
                        <p>
                        "Spoon Theory" describes an analogy used by some chronically ill and disabled individuals to help others 
                         - often to those without chronic health conditions - understand the necessity chronically ill individuals 
                        have of budgeting their limited energy supply and planning activities so as not to run out of energy.  
                        The analogy involves starting each day with a number of spoons, or energy, and planning how to use them, with 
                        some activities using spoons, like taking a walk, and activities restoring spoons, like taking a nap.  Spoon Theory 
                        was first used and documented in 2003 by Christine Miserandino, an American writer, lupus sufferer, and 
                        activist.  <a href="https://butyoudontlooksick.com/articles/written-by-christine/the-spoon-theory/#google_vignette">For more information</a>
                        </p> 
